name: Nami Rasa Restaurant
address: Buruan, Penebel, Tabanan Regency, Bali 82181, Indonesia

review 2: Lots of different items to choose from, great for a quick lunch.
review 3:

Good balinese and general indonesian food. Very moderate in price.
Only the toilets have been not in a good condition.

review 4: cozy restaurant with many Balinese food selection, buffet style, you pick your food and they will give you a price card. The food in here is amazingly good, always fresh and delicious, my only complaint is the flies.
review 5: The best clean and delicious food in Penebel area. The price for the buffet food and others are affordable. All facilities are good maintained inc. the Toilet is clean. Friendly staff and the parking area is spacious and also it's free of charge.

name: Warung Nasi Nanang Mang
address: Jl. Batukaru No.115, Buruan, Kec. Penebel, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82181, Indonesia
review 1:
This place serves balinese food based on pork. If you are a pork eater, you should try it. They have everything made by pork.

My favorite is pork Genyol and pork soto. They are delicious.

Do not expect 5 star hotel service if you want to eat here. It is very local and homemade. You also can see the kitchen. The owner will allow you if u ask permission to.

If you come at rush hour, be patient for getting a seat.
review 2: This place has a lot of menus to dine in or takeaway and tastes good üëç
review 3: Good food with good price. Portion is average but provide selection of spicy pork, spicy chicken or spicy fish combine with steamed rice and "Lawar" traditional Balinesse salad or "Pecel" Javanesse traditional salad.
review 4: Very delicious balinese food with afordable price
review 5: reasonably priced aka cheap üôÇ. tasty. pork, fish, chicken, lawar

name: Jaje bali jaen
address: Jl. Batukaru No.115, Buruan, Kec. Penebel, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82152, Indonesia
review 1:
If you are looking for balinese traditional snack, this is the right place. They serve bali coffee and you may choose many snack. The taste is delicous. Keplon, two kind of bubur sumsum and many others that i can't remember the names. But i am sure you will remember the looks because the form of snack is very significant.

If you ask about the cleanliness, i can assure you that it is clean. They do not use artificial color. They use a kind of plant leaf, daun suci for snack's color.
